><A HREF="gc.htm"> Of God and His Creatures</a><hr><p>
There is some limit to the application of this
principle. A dumb animal could not be raised to the
supernatural order. Short of intellectual soul, there
can be no sanctifying grace. Unless the mind's eye
be naturally open to intellectual truth, there is no
means of opening it to the vision of God.

